The Civil Rights Association issued a travel warning for Missouri .
The National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP) has issued a travel advisory for Missouri, citing discriminatory practices and racist attacks in the state.
NAACP's Missouri Travel Information, effective August 28, 2017, urges African-American travelers, visitors and locals to exercise extreme caution and caution when traveling in the state that has recently experienced a number of questionable racially motivated incidents, the NAACP said in a statement.
