When Svenska Dagbladet analysed the same results, it was found that in 243 cases the applicant had openly stated that he would be 18 this year.
The medical method used in the tests to assess age is to take X-rays of wisdom teeth and magnetic images of the kneecaps, which are then analyzed by dentists and radiologists.
One of the skeptics is Claude Marcus, an endocrinologist at the Karolinska Institute, whose work involves assessing the biological maturity of humans, which can determine whether a person has reached puberty earlier or later than normal.
I have had reason to think about it and I do not think the method used is right.
Determining biological age in this way is highly uncertain.
If we can't determine age for sure, we shouldn't pretend we can", he told the Metro newspaper.
However, the forensic science office, Göransson, defended the accuracy of the tests: In general, the risk of identifying a child as an adult is low.
